hmKeywords:"axpsnap,bifurcate,boot,bootPC,checksum,cleanPC,copyLoop,copyLoopMs,copyLoopSteps,cyclesExecuted,decompress,decompressor,deterministic,donePC,elapsedMs,emulatorBuildId,ES40,ES45,EV6,finalPalBase,finalPC,FNV,fromSnapshot,GetFpRegsFn,GetIntRegsFn,GetIprsFn,GetU64Fn,headerSkip,initSteps,IPR,IprPair,isLoaded,JSR,kCopyExitPC,kCopyLoopPC,kDecompSig,kSnapshotMagic,kSnapshotVersion,loadFromFile,loadPA,loadSnapshot,maxSteps,mirrorPA,PAL,PAL_BASE,palBase,PALcode,payload,payloadSize,postCopySteps,ProgressFn,QDataStream,QSettings,ReadPhysicalFn,romHash,runloop,saveSnapshot,SetFpRegsFn,SetIntRegsFn,SetIprsFn,SetU64Fn,SingleStepFn,snapshot,snapshotPath,SrmBase,SRM-D,SrmDonePC,SrmInitialPC,SrmLoaderConfig,SrmMaxSteps,SrmMirrorPA,SrmRomLoader,SrmRomLoadResult,SrmSnapshot,SrmSnapshotDir,SrmSnapshotMemRegion,startPC,success,USE_EMBEDDED_SRM,useEmbedded,WritePhysicalFn",
hmTitle:"Appendix J – SRM Snapshot Machinery (SRM-D)",
hmDescription:"This appendix is the authoritative reference for the SRM Decompressed Snapshot subsystem — referred to throughout the project as SRM-D. SRM-D provides a bifurcated boot path...",
